                                      ASSIGNMENT-4

Q-1. What is Programming language?
Ans- Programming language is a language/way for a programmer/developer to communicate with computer machine.

Q-2. Why do we need a programming language?
Ans- we need a programming language to communicate with computer for accomplish our desire tasks.

Q-3. What are the features of Java?
Ans- Features of Java :-
     Platform independent
     Simple
     Object-oriented
     Portable
     Distributed,etc.

Q-4. What is an Object?
Ans- Object is anything around us like table,chair,etc. Either it is tangible
     and intangible.

Q-5. What is a class?
Ans- Class is a collection of similar things like example- Animal,Student,etc.
 
Q-6. Explain about the main() method in Java?
Ans-The Java main method is usually the first method you learn about 
    when you start programming in Java because its the entry point for executing a Java program,
    It is predefined in JVM.
 
